Round Mountain first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2000 U.S. census]].<ref name=2000CensusCA/>

===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Round Mountain had a population of 160. The population density was {{convert|95.4|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Round Mountain was 126 (78.8%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 14 (8.8%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 3 (1.9%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 1 (0.6%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 16 (10.0%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 14 persons (8.8%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Round Mountain CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0663134 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 1, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 75 households, out of which 11 (14.7%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 32 (42.7%) were married-couple households, 11 (14.7%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 21 (28.0%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 11 (14.7%) had a male householder with no partner present. 17 households (22.7%) were one person, and 9 (12.0%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.13.<ref name=DP1/> There were 45 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (60.0% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Round Mountain CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0663134 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 1, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 19 people (11.9%) under the age of 18, 12 people (7.5%) aged 18 to 24, 24 people (15.0%) aged 25 to 44, 58 people (36.2%) aged 45 to 64, and 47 people (29.4%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 54.2{{nbsp}}years. There were 77 males and 83 females.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 83 housing units at an average density of {{convert|49.5|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 75 (90.4%) were occupied. Of these, 62 (82.7%) were owner-occupied, and 13 (17.3%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
At the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]] Round Mountain had a population of 155. The population density was {{convert|92.1|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Round Mountain was 126 (81.3%) White, 2 (0.6%) African American, 12 (7.7%) Native American, 3 (1.9%) Asian, 1 (0.6%) Pacific Islander, 1 (0.6%) from other races, and 11 (7.1%) from two or more races.  Hispanic or Latino of any race were 12 people (7.7%).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0663134|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715032827/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0663134|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Round Mountain CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|accessdate=July 12, 2014}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households, no one lived in non-institutionalized group quarters and no one was institutionalized.

There were 74 households, 14 (18.9%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 27 (36.5%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 4 (5.4%) had a female householder with no husband present, 5 (6.8%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 4 (5.4%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 1 (1.4%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 31 households (41.9%) were one person and 12 (16.2%) had someone living alone who was 65 or older. The average household size was 2.09.  There were 36 families (48.6% of households); the average family size was 2.92.

The age distribution was 27 people (17.4%) under the age of 18, 12 people (7.7%) aged 18 to 24, 30 people (19.4%) aged 25 to 44, 55 people (35.5%) aged 45 to 64, and 31 people (20.0%) who were 65 or older.  The median age was 47.8 years. For every 100 females, there were 98.7 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 106.5 males.

There were 82 housing units at an average density of 48.7 per square mile, of the occupied units 57 (77.0%) were owner-occupied and 17 (23.0%) were rented. The homeowner vacancy rate was 1.7%; the rental vacancy rate was 5.3%.  113 people (72.9% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 42 people (27.1%) lived in rental housing units.

===2000===
At the [[2000 United States census|2000 census]], the median household income was $18,250 and the median family income  was $28,125. Males had a median income of $36,250 versus $28,750 for females. The per capita income for the CDP was $9,598. There were 25.9% of families and 28.0% of the population living below the [[poverty line]], including no under eighteens and 13.3% of those over 64.<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref>

